About this item

  • SLIP-RESISTANT WORK SHOES FOR WOMEN & MEN: The unisex Zone are classic clogs for men and women that feature Anywear’s signature lightweight design, plentiful cushioning, and comfortable roomy toe box. Swivel back strap for a secure and adjustable fit. These nursing shoes are easy to clean with soap and warm water. Heel height = 1 ½"
  • THE SIZES, COLORS, AND PATTERNS YOU WANT: These men's and women’s clogs are available in numerous colors and prints to coordinate with your style, vibe, and uniform. Select colors also available in a wide width. As versatile as they are comfortable, perfect nursing, food service, and garden shoes
  • EXCEPTIONAL CUSHION AND SHOCK ABSORPTION: The Anywear Zone slingback nurse shoes for women and men are made of an injection molded EVA upper and midsole for outstanding cushioning and shock absorption. The EVA construction provides comfortable wear, durability, and quick clean-up. Designed for healthcare workers, the Zone also makes great non slip shoes for food service workers
  • SWEAT-REDUCING REMOVABLE INSOLE: These nurse clogs have a removable insole so you can customize your fit. The insole lining has treatment and ventilation holes to prevent odor and promote air circulation and help keep your feet comfortable
  • SLIP-RESISTANT OUTSOLE: Anywear Zone slip-resistant shoes for women and men feature a high-friction outsole with non-slip pads and water evacuation channels to give you the stability you need during a hectic work shift – just what the doctor ordered!

    Great for me, although I can see why other's may have an issue. Buy with end use in mind.
    Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2016
    Size: 9 Women/7 MenColor: Navy
    One caveat, you need socks with these. They are not animal products, but because of that, they have no give in the size department and do not breath. I use them when I am dying yarn and need to be on my feet all day. I wear cotton socks that are somewhat thin. While... See more
    One caveat, you need socks with these. They are not animal products, but because of that, they have no give in the size department and do not breath. I use them when I am dying yarn and need to be on my feet all day. I wear cotton socks that are somewhat thin. While comfortable, if you cannot wear them day one, they will not break in. I am not sure if I was cutting hair, or a nurse, that these would work. I can slip them off if my feet get hot, I work from home, no harm, no foul. If I could not take them off for a few minutes every couple of hours, I know I would get blisters. So, while they are comfortable for me and I can stand in them all day, even if I am in a booth selling, I am not sure walking around in them all day would be as comfortable. My perfect, is for what I do, I know a lot of the other reviews mention the problems above. Again, they are not issues for me, but I have no doubt that they might be for some. I do love them, though and want more. I wear them almost everyday at home. .

    The shoes look decent and are comfortable to wear. I believe they would be even more comfortable if the size was correct. I have read mixed reviews on this. Some say they run big some say they run too small. This pair I received ran TOO BIG. I agree with the reviews that say they should offer half sizes. I usually wear an 8 and if they offered a 7.5 I would have gotten that size. Since they are a tad bit too big my foot slides my toes into the top of the shoe. It's just annoying and I'm worried the shoe will just fall off even though I know it won't with the strap on. Speaking of the strap, it is too big as well and does not touch my heel at all. Again, I believe this could be fixed with a smaller size. I have only worn these two days so I can't comment on whether the color stays on the shoe after a scuff or not. SO far so good though.
    UPDATE:
    The size of the shoe does not bother me as much as I thought it would. The shoe is very comfortable and my feet never hurt. I am dragging it down to one star though because they make my feet sweat and smell terrible. I have never had this problem with any shoe and my feet have never smelled before. I got so sick of it I took the insert that came with it out and there was MOLD GROWING UNDERNEATH. Yes, there was mold in between the insert and the shoe. I am not pleased with this finding and I do not recommend this shoe to anyone.
